Bao Bao, the four and a half month old giant panda, makes her public debut at an indoor habitat at the National Zoo in Washington. (Charles Dharapak, AP) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Washington - The National Zoo will be saying bye-bye to panda cub Bao Bao. The zoo said Thursday that Bao Bao will move to China within the first few months of 2017. Part of the zoo's co-operative breeding agreement with the China Wildlife Conservation Association is that all cubs born at the zoo move to China by the time they turn 4 years old. Bao Bao will turn 4 on August 23 2017. Bao Bao is the first surviving cub born at the zoo since 2005. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  